loving lately ✨👇🏻 

took a MUCH needed full week break from social! lucia is FINALLY feeling better after being sick for the past 2+ weeks (nothing is worse than seeing your baby sick 🥺) and i couldn’t feel more relieved. 

i didn’t have the time or energy for full on skincare routines but these 3 products kept my skin healthy, hydrated & GLOWING.

💦 @youthtothepeople triple peptide + cactus oasis serum: this is quite literally a tall drink of water for your skin. a super lightweight formula it seriously feels like your applying water for instant hydration! my skin drinks this right up & feels baby soft and smooth everytime i use this! gimme alllllll the hyaluronic acid 👏🏻 
🥛 @beekman1802 oh! mega milk facial oil: unlike most facial oils, this has a milky and super lightweight formula! it never leaves my skin feeling greasy or too oily as it absorbs immediately into the skin leaving it with the prettiest glow! i use it at night and wake up with a super luminous complexion 🤌🏻
🌙 @summerfridays jet lag mask: this is pricey but my absolute go-to for a 1-step PM skincare routine. when i am lazy or too exhausted (almost every night let’s be real 😂) i just use this. it’s super rich texture feels like butter on the skin and leaves it feeling so soft and plump! the hype is real on this one!

fav retinol-alternatives🤱🏻🍼

i am still breastfeeding (exclusive pumper over here 💪🏻) so still refraining from using my beloved retinol — here are my current favs that are keeping my skin in check 👇🏻 

🥛 @beekman1802 midnight milk better aging sleep mask: newest to my PM skincare routine! it’s a super lightweight gel formula (it’s purple 💜!!) that is meant to be used as the last step of your PM routine. i’ll apply this after my face cream (my holy grail @farmacybeauty honey halo) and when i wake up in the AM my skin has been looking and feeling more plump and firm!
💜 @renskincare bio retinoid youth serum: a watery serum that absorbs immediately and never irritates my sensitive postpartum skin! it’s helped keep acne at bay and has helped keep my skin in check with its plant based retinol alternative. such a nice formula!
🌙 @herbivorebotanicals moon dew eye cream: this baby is THICK but so easy to apply and blend out under my delicate undereye area. never gives me milia (little bumps from super thick creams) and has helped tame my fine lines and crows feet 🙊 

shout out to my fellow breastfeeding mamas — it is HARD. WORK. but so so worth it. 🤍

when you can’t pick just one 🤍

happy belated Mother’s Day to all my fellow mamas. motherhood is the craziest ride i’ve ever been on in the best way possible. this girly is more than i could have ever dreamed of and i am so lucky to be her mommy 🥹

from sleepless nights and middle of the night feedings, witching hours and what feels like endless pump sessions, to contact naps and morning snuggles, her first smile and even better that first giggle, to all her new milestones and experiencing the world through her eyes, it just keeps getting better and better. torn between wanting to freeze time and keep her this little forever and so excited to watch her grow up! 

here’s to all the mamas, you are all warriors 💪🏻

REVIEW: @snif.co crumb couture🫐🥐 

after using this for over a month now i am FINALLY sharing my review on this secret menu perfume from snif — meaning it’s not on their website but if you Google it, it’ll come up. 🤫 

after initially spraying it on my skin, i immediately smell the croissant and sweet gourmand notes (toasted vanilla + tonka bean). it’s a strong punch of sweetness at first but it then dries down and i get those berry notes (wild berry jam, black currant) mixed with the note of musky sandalwood. 

it doesn’t last that long on the skin but i find myself getting whiffs of it in my hair and on my clothes throughout the day! it reminds me of what a bakery smells like — a mix of sweet pastries, vanilla & fresh fruit 🫐 

i think i realized with this perfume i’m not a huge gourmand girl. this perfume is a really nice cozy scent that will be great for fall and winter but i don’t think i’d reach for it in the spring or summer — only really wearing it now at home around the house lol. 

overall, i enjoy this but it’s not on my list of favorite perfumes! $65 is a lot for a “cozy at home perfume” but it does make me feel more put together when i do wear it around the house if that makes any sense 😂 

i think if you love sweet scents then you’d love this one. have you tried it? LMK in the comments 🥐
